      "role": "user",
      "content": "i've been watching the starlings in the park every morning for like three weeks now and it's not just random movement. they're actually signaling the pressure changes with their flight patterns way before the barometers even move. i saw it clearly this morning—the way they were circling in that tight spiral meant a storm was coming within the hour, and it happened exactly like that. it's like they have this whole language for the weather that nobody else is paying attention to.",
